Response ID: resp_704
Response Text: Per our music community, we'd love to see more city-sponsored music events that adhere to the city standard pay rate that Austin Texas Musicians established in 2023. The work that Greg Gonzalez and Shelbi Mitchell are doing in the Music Division to bolster paid performance opportunities should be lauded; Additionally, more financial support for the AUS Airport music program would be helpful, as this is in fact the largest employer of musicians in Austin. Finally, support for arts nonprofits events through increased STR HOT revenue would go a long way in our music community: HAAM Day has now become the largest one-day music festival in the world and will soon have a Guinness record to celebrate this fact, while other nonprofits like Red River Cultural District and many more create outstanding tourist-facing paid performance opportunities. With SXSW now focusing efforts outside of Austin, an increased investment in supporting pad performance events through arts nonprofits will be key to sustaining Austin's brand and resulting tourism and business economies.

